                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="13695737" author="stack" created="Fri, 28 Jun 2013 20:06:20 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Helping you out Lars, saving you work.... The embedded project is a failed effort that should not be perpetuated.  See Karthik here: &lt;a href=&quot;http://search-hadoop.com/m/GAFt6B9CRZ&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;http://search-hadoop.com/m/GAFt6B9CRZ&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Resolving as &apos;wont fix&apos;; reopen if I have it wrong Lars?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13695771" author="larsgeorge" created="Fri, 28 Jun 2013 20:45:36 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Oh, good to know, we leave it at that then, unless someone objects.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13697788" author="larsgeorge" created="Tue, 2 Jul 2013 13:42:23 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hey &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=saint.ack%40gmail.com&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;saint.ack@gmail.com&quot;&gt;Stack&lt;/a&gt;, I am not sure I understand why this is a failed effort. Reading Karthik&apos;s email, he just makes a point to bypass Thrift all together, so that a client can talk natively to the APIs - which is now possible since we use ProtoBufs everywhere. But for those not using that path, but need to use REST or Thrift as a gateway, why is embedding the ThriftServer a failed effort? Could you kindly clarify?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13698102" author="stack" created="Tue, 2 Jul 2013 18:58:45 +0000"  >&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;But for those not using that path, but need to use REST or Thrift as a gateway, why is embedding the ThriftServer a failed effort? Could you kindly clarify?&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The overhead of bringing along the embedded gateway when changes internal or in api was too burdensome.  They abandoned the effort.  No one else is working on it.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
